Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
# --- GTK4 + libadwaita runtime ----------------------------------------
# The wizard is written in Python with PyGObject bindings against
# libadwaita (so it follows the GNOME visual language). The Trixie
# stack:
#   python3-gi               PyGObject 3.50
#   gir1.2-gtk-4.0           GTK 4 typelib
#   gir1.2-adw-1             libadwaita 1.5 typelib
#   libadwaita-1-0           libadwaita runtime
 python3-gi,
 gir1.2-gtk-4.0,
 gir1.2-adw-1,
 libadwaita-1-0,
# --- PolicyKit for the elevated `apt install` calls ------------------
# The wizard runs as the user, then drives apt via pkexec with a custom
# policy (shipped in files/). On Trixie the legacy policykit-1 transition
# package has been retired — depend on the actual daemon + pkexec
# directly.
 polkitd,
 pkexec,
# --- apt itself (for the install call) -------------------------------
 apt,
Description: AIMS OS — first-boot wizard (track + extras selection)
 Installs the first-boot wizard that lets a fresh AIMS OS user pick
 their track (Regular Maths, Coop Big Data, Coop Computer Security)
 and any optional desktop extras (Chromium, GIMP, Inkscape, …) or
 the heavy dev stack (Java, Android, Docker, …).
 .
 The wizard auto-starts at the first GNOME session via an XDG
 autostart entry, checks connectivity, then runs `apt install` via
 pkexec with a bundled policy. After the first successful run it
 marks itself done in ~/.config/aims-welcome.done and stays silent
 unless the user re-launches it from the app grid.
 .
 This is the wiring layer; the actual Python source for the wizard
 lives under files/usr/share/aims-os-welcome/ and ships with this
 package (added in step 4 of the v2.1 plan).
